Henderson et al. v. East Tenn., Va. & Ga. Rwy. Co. This case falls within the general rule that the first grant of a new trial by the presiding judge will not be reversed. March 26, 1894.

Argued at the last term.

Complaint for land. Before Judge Henry. Floyd superior court. September term, 1892. T. W. Alexander and Hooper Alexander, for plaintiffs. McCutchen & Shumate, Hoskinson & Harris and C. N. Featherston, for defendant.

Judgment affirmed.
